article.headline: Va. Commonwealth 91, Elon 49
article.story: ELON, N.C. (AP) -- Eric Maynor scored 15 points and grabbed six rebounds Tuesday to lead five players for Virginia Commonwealth in double figures as the Rams beat Elon 91-49. The 4-2 Rams held a 22-0 lead with 11:56 left in the first half and never trailed. Also scoring in double digits for the Rams were B.A. Walker with 14 points, T.J. Gwynn with 13, Jesse Pellot-Rosa with 11 and Michael Anderson with 10. Elon's Devan Carter had 19 points for the 1-4 Phoenix.
